<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<configuration>
  <runtime>
    <!--
      Tekla.* assemblies are supplied at runtime by TeklaAssemblyResolver (see Program.cs).

      Do NOT add bindingRedirects that point Tekla.* at an unreachable version (the old
      2999.9.9.9 anti-GAC trick). It is fundamentally incompatible with the byte-loading
      resolver: on .NET Framework, Assembly.Load(byte[]) APPLIES binding policy to the image's
      identity, so the redirect turns the resolver's own load into a bind for 2999.9.9.9 —
      a circular resolve that ends in FileNotFound/StackOverflow (verified live, twice:
      cbe716b and the d167ff4 re-attempt reverted right after).

      KNOWN LIMITATION until per-version builds land: without the redirects, a stale GAC copy
      at the compile-baseline version binds silently past the resolver and the dedicated tools
      fail against a newer running Tekla (issue #7). EnsureTeklaReady logs a loud stderr
      warning when that happens; the interim workaround is to remove the stale Tekla
      assemblies from the GAC. The planned fix is per-Tekla-version release builds, where the
      requested assembly version always matches the installed Tekla.
    -->
  </runtime>
</configuration>
